    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for high offensive output today, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (77.15) and **Gunnar Henderson** (76.62). **Kyle Tucker** leads the unit as the most reliable start, benefiting from an elite xwOBA (.372) and a favorable matchup against Clay Holmes. **Gunnar Henderson** also projects for a standout performance; while he faces a difficult left-on-left matchup against Ed Rodriguez, the combination of a significant park factor (+16%) and wind blowing out (+5%) keeps his efficiency well within the elite tier. **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) rounds out our top trio, offering high upside despite a slight penalty for facing an elite hold pitcher.\n\nWe are navigating a few high-risk matchups against top-tier arms. **Jorge Polanco** (42.86) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (42.11) see their value heavily suppressed by facing Shohei Ohtani (2.67 xERA). While we are counting on their talent to bridge the gap, they are barely clearing our efficiency floor. The most difficult bench decision involved **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.15). He was the clear standout on the pine, offering strong raw projections, but he was ultimately squeezed out by the depth of our outfield and the efficiency of **Josh Lowe** (71.68), whose platoon advantage against Gil (+14%) provided the necessary edge to justify the start.\n\nManagers should monitor the lineup status for **Marcell Ozuna** closely; his score of 61.94 is threatened by a 37% rain risk. We are also keeping an eye on the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Jacob Wilson**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Andy Pages**. While our projections are modeled on their typical batting positions, any drop in the order would necessitate a re-evaluation of their projected R and RBI output. Ensure **Marcell Ozuna** is cleared for weather before the first pitch, as any delay could impact our daily game cap management strategy.",
